# PDV

The [color=tan]Phaethon Dynasty Imperial Vanguard[/color] is an isolated monarchy located in the Colossus sector and possibly adjacent bodies of space that are currently deemed undiscovered. Initially a group of feudal bodies lost to the history books, now a large Sultanate regime wielding old syndicate technologies scavenged after the Corporate War's conclusion. Known as the native inhabitants of the Perseus Arm, they are hell bent on evicting the [color=cyan]Trans-Solarian-Federation Marine Corps[/color] and obtaining complete control over the independent industries of Colossus.

   Fueled by an ever-growing industry and their reverse-engineered equipment littering their territory, the empire wield their ballistic weaponry with a heavy and unforgiving hand.

   While smaller in number compared to the broader [color=cyan]TSFMC[/color], the [color=tan]empire[/color] is nowhere near weak in comparison to their foes detache that are nearly entirely stranded at their doorstep, it is a boon that their sectors [color=pink]anomalous activities[/color] prevents their enemies from gaining the upper hand.

   They are capable of using their mobility and brutal tactics to separate their enemies in number and eliminate them one by one until they are victorious. No cost too great, every death repaid with interest, that is the way their Sultan's [color=purple]Grand Vizier[/color](s) operate.

   The [color=tan]Phaethon Dynasty Imperial Vanguard[/color] has been given a simple directive by their commanding Sultanate:

  > [bold][color=red]Destabilize the region to prepare it for Dynasty occupation.[/bold][/color]


# Hierarchy (I-V)

   As important as the Sultan's goals are to the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color] there is no way to succeed without a pecking order. Performance with purpose is the only way to succeed in warfare and the Sultanate understands this well. Follow the [color=tan]PDV[/color]'s and crushing enemies of the [color=tan]Dynasty[/color] will be much easier. 

(I)   [color=purple]Grand Vizier[/color] is the [bold]highest ranking[/bold] within the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color] and closest to the Sultanate of the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color]. They have the final say in any matter regarding operations. Denying the request of a Vizier is no different from high treason to the [color=tan]empire[/color]. While the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color] is capable of acting without a leader to direct their fury there is nothing more terrifying than a leader who can rally their soldiers.

   It does not matter how the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color] is victorious, only that it is, ensure the Sultan's wishes are reality and that honor is upheld through even the newest of bloods.

(II)   [color=yellow]Asvaran[/color] are the [bold]second highest[/bold] among the [color=tan]PDV[/color] and answers exclusively to the [color=purple]Grand Vizier[/color]. Their duty consists of delegating work within the fold and defending their [color=tan]Vanguard[/color]'s aforementioned head of operation.

(III)   [color=gold]Denasvar[/color], while not much more than the average foot soldier, is considered a more experienced and leadership capable position. They are generally picked above others for leading smaller detachments of [color=orange]Rahkshan[/color]. Be the guiding force across the frontline.

(IV)   [color=orange]Rahkshan[/color] are arguably the backbone of the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color]. Necessary for success because without a foot soldier you have no army. You are the rage of the Sultan. Act with purpose and follow the will of the [color=purple]Grand Vizier[/color]. Dying in the heat of combat is the highest honor. Living to reap the benefits of the Sultan's many victories, large and small, is a privilege.

(IV-I)   [color=red]Spasaka[/color]. You shouldn't encounter [color=red]Spasaka[/color] in any event, at least not without them allowing it, as they often disguise themselves even to their own peers to ensure their identity is ambiguous. Specialists designed around infiltration and espionage. They are equipped with old Syndicate agent technology capable of altering many aspects of their persona. One thing that a [color=red]Spasaka[/color] must always do, however, is ensure that their goals are in line with their commanders. Keeping close contact with the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color] during their work is key to proper information gathering and window opening.

(V)  [color=gray]Cyborgs[/color] are automatons capable of assisting in various fields. Constructed by the finest minds of the empirical [color=tan]Dynasty[/color] and ready to serve any orders given to them by the [color=tan]Vanguard[/color].

