   Armor of the [color=tan]Dynasty[/color] shares a backstory much like their firearms. Reverse-engineered, mass-produced, low-tech and effective. At least for the most part. Some equipment has very specific tendencies. It is important to pick and choose.

  [color=green]Strengths:[/color]
  - being low-tech means armor is fairly simple. Whatever has the better mobility or better defense is what suits the user. Pairing a good set of protection can determine your combat capabilities with your primary firearm.
  - There is little limit to the options at hand. Stealth, juggernaut, you name it. The [color=tan]empire[/color] has probably tried.

  [color=red]Weaknesses:[/color]
  - Just like the weaponry, there is no objectively good armor, you have to prepare what is available with what is necessary.
